ht. Karin Hostettler arbeitet das mit diesem Denken verbundene Othering und die damit einhergehende Selbstaffirmation heraus und zeigt so die Selbstverortung der kritischen Philosophie in einer kolonialen Episteme auf.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPhilosophy. 4aAnti-Imperialismus. 4aDeutsche Philosophiegeschichte. 4aFreiheit. 4aGeschichtsphilosophie. 4aImmanuel Kant. 4aKritische Materialität. 4aKultur. 4aNatur. 4aNaturteleologie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophische Anthropologie. 4aPostkoloniale Studien. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aRassismus. 4aVernunft. 4aZweckmäßigkeit. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aAnti Imperialism.  aCritical Materiality.  aCulture.  aGerman History of Philosophy.  aImmanuel Kant.  aLiberty.  aNature.  aNatureteleoligy.  aPhilosophical Anthropology.  aPhilosophy of History.  aPhilosophy.  aPostcolonial Studies.  aPostcolonialism.  aRacism.  aReason.  aSuitability.2 aSwiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH0 cprintz978383765176840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839451762?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839451762zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97838394517